WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.417
[pages riffling]

00:08.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ dramatic theme playing ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:14.958
♪

00:19.417 --> 00:23.500
OZU: [on loudspeaker]
Honor! Tradition! Values!

00:24.875 --> 00:28.125
Don't forget to vote tomorrow,
my friends!

00:28.750 --> 00:31.750
The future of Japan depends on it!

00:31.750 --> 00:32.750
[Monkey shrieking]

00:32.750 --> 00:35.000
[people screaming]

00:35.000 --> 00:36.333
‐ Stop that monkey!

00:36.333 --> 00:38.208
[panting]

00:40.292 --> 00:42.042
[hooting, screeching]

00:44.542 --> 00:46.792
‐ The monkey's headed
towards Yoyogi Park.

00:46.792 --> 00:47.708
Send backup.

00:48.750 --> 00:53.042
♪

00:53.875 --> 00:55.833
BRYCE:
You're a Halloween costume now?

00:55.833 --> 00:56.417
[ooks]

00:57.167 --> 00:58.125
Hey, no bullshit.

00:58.500 --> 00:59.583
Old Bryce

01:00.083 --> 01:01.917
would have been totally jealous
of this moment.

01:01.917 --> 01:03.000
[grunts]

01:03.000 --> 01:04.333
[camera shutter clicking]

01:04.333 --> 01:08.208
♪ dramatic theme playing ♪

01:08.208 --> 01:12.083
♪

01:18.625 --> 01:20.083
[Monkey whimpers]
[whistles]

01:20.083 --> 01:21.583
Holy moley.

01:22.667 --> 01:23.792
I don't mean to sound
like I'm bragging,

01:23.792 --> 01:25.667
but, well, you know,
this isn't the first time

01:25.667 --> 01:27.125
a woman's
burned down my pad.

01:27.583 --> 01:28.833
[ooking]

01:28.833 --> 01:30.917
Hey, look, if we're going to track
and kill Lady Bullseye,

01:30.917 --> 01:32.375
we're going to need
our weapons, so let's get‐‐

01:32.375 --> 01:33.542
Oh‐whoa.

01:35.250 --> 01:37.625
Okay, well,
this is not normal. Whoa!

01:37.625 --> 01:40.958
Hey, look at this!
It's like some Back to the Future shit‐‐

01:40.958 --> 01:42.458
What the hell was that?

01:42.458 --> 01:44.167
[grunting]

01:44.167 --> 01:45.917
Uh, nothing.
Nothing. Sorry. No, I‐I‐‐

01:45.917 --> 01:48.208
You know, I thought I saw
a two‐headed squirrel run by.

01:48.208 --> 01:49.750
But it, uh, it was just a, uh,

01:50.125 --> 01:50.958
a one‐headed‐‐

01:50.958 --> 01:52.708
Doesn't matter. Look, are you
gonna grab the guns or what?

01:52.708 --> 01:53.375
Come on,
let's go, man.

01:53.375 --> 01:55.583
[grunting]

01:55.583 --> 01:56.792
What do you mean
there's no weapons?

01:56.792 --> 01:57.875
They're gone?

01:57.875 --> 01:58.917
[Monkey grunts]
Shit.

01:59.250 --> 02:02.208
The police must have gone through
this place with a fine‐toothed comb.

02:02.208 --> 02:02.958
OFFICER:
Freeze!

02:02.958 --> 02:04.417
‐ Oh, Jesus.
[ooks]

02:04.417 --> 02:05.958
BRYCE: What is this,
another cop?

02:06.458 --> 02:07.792
Scared the hell outta me.

02:07.792 --> 02:09.208
[growls]
OFFICER: Drop it!

02:10.708 --> 02:11.792
AKIKO:
Relax.

02:13.500 --> 02:15.042
She's on our side.

02:15.750 --> 02:17.042
[grunts]
BRYCE: Well, well, well.

02:17.667 --> 02:19.792
The game is afoot, huh?

02:19.792 --> 02:20.792
[chuckles]

02:22.458 --> 02:24.583
[ooks]

02:26.958 --> 02:28.542
‐ I'm happy to see you too.

02:29.250 --> 02:30.833
A lot's happened
since you've been gone.

02:30.833 --> 02:32.042
‐ So, to catch you up,

02:32.042 --> 02:34.625
I've been going through
The Rooster's blackmail,

02:34.625 --> 02:36.417
and I found
something interesting.

02:36.417 --> 02:37.083
[grunts]

02:37.083 --> 02:39.167
‐ Is... is that blood?

02:39.583 --> 02:40.333
[shrieks]

02:40.333 --> 02:42.042
‐ Would you just die already!

02:42.042 --> 02:43.750
[Monkey shrieks]
[screams]

02:45.667 --> 02:46.917
‐ Oh‐ho, man.

02:46.917 --> 02:49.250
Not so sure
about Encyclopedia Brown over here.

02:49.542 --> 02:51.958
I mean, that box
is literally overflowing

02:51.958 --> 02:54.083
with dirt on the most
powerful players in Japan,

02:54.083 --> 02:55.458
and she's focused
on the pen?

02:55.458 --> 02:56.292
[grunts]

02:56.292 --> 02:58.500
‐ This seemingly innocuous pen

02:58.500 --> 03:00.500
is actually a recording device.
‐ A recording device!

03:00.500 --> 03:01.542
No, that makes more sense.

03:02.458 --> 03:05.500
MAN:
If Ken Takahara wins this election,

03:05.500 --> 03:10.000
his anti‐corruption measures
will destroy your organization.

03:10.000 --> 03:12.125
ROOSTER:
Hey, the Rooster's no fool.

03:12.125 --> 03:13.750
I get what's in it for me,

03:13.750 --> 03:15.000
but what about you?

03:15.458 --> 03:18.792
Why are you and your associate
doing this?

03:19.333 --> 03:21.583
MAN:
That is not your concern.

03:23.333 --> 03:25.833
Just get rid of him.

03:25.833 --> 03:26.958
‐ Holy shit.

03:30.375 --> 03:31.792
It's Bonsai Shoes!

03:33.125 --> 03:36.333
‐ The man you just heard order
the hit is named Ichiro Hazaki,

03:36.333 --> 03:38.417
but he's better known
as "The Bonsai Master."

03:38.417 --> 03:40.958
‐ Eh, Master. Shoes.
Potato, tomato. Whatever.

03:40.958 --> 03:42.250
[grunting]

03:42.250 --> 03:43.417
‐ He's a big deal
in the political world

03:43.417 --> 03:46.083
and by far the biggest donor
to Ozu's campaign.

03:46.333 --> 03:47.917
He's the brains
behind all this.

03:48.375 --> 03:50.833
‐ Haruka hasn't gone to the police
with this recording.

03:50.833 --> 03:52.417
We're the only ones
who know the truth.

03:52.417 --> 03:55.500
‐ I brought it to you because
we both have friends to avenge.

03:55.750 --> 03:57.458
And God knows
the police aren't going to help.

03:57.458 --> 03:59.042
‐ If we don't stop these guys,

03:59.375 --> 04:01.750
my uncle will be
the next to die.

04:02.625 --> 04:03.750
We need your help.

04:07.833 --> 04:10.667
[growls]

04:12.292 --> 04:13.750
‐ Does that mean he's in?

04:13.750 --> 04:16.208
‐ Oh. Oh yeah. Yeah, yeah,
that's an "I'm in" growl for sure.

04:16.667 --> 04:17.792
We're good.
BRYCE: Hey, psst.

04:18.708 --> 04:19.917
Tell 'em I'm in, too.

04:20.750 --> 04:25.375
♪

04:35.125 --> 04:40.625
♪

04:43.375 --> 04:46.625
‐ Bonsai Master's compound is
in the foothills of Mount Takao.

04:46.625 --> 04:48.000
It's heavily guarded.

04:48.000 --> 04:50.458
Tonight he'll be there hosting
the official watch party

04:50.458 --> 04:51.625
for Ozu's campaign.

04:51.625 --> 04:54.833
‐ It is a beautiful background
for a concession speech.

04:55.083 --> 04:57.292
Too bad he's not going
to be around to make it.

04:57.292 --> 04:58.333
[ooks]

04:58.333 --> 04:59.958
What? Too dark?

04:59.958 --> 05:01.708
‐ Eh‐‐
‐ Not for me. I love it.

05:02.167 --> 05:03.542
This chick
is growing on me.

05:03.542 --> 05:06.625
‐ I, uh, found this beneath
what used to be my sofa.

05:06.958 --> 05:07.833
[ooks]

05:07.833 --> 05:09.042
Figured you might need it.

05:09.375 --> 05:10.792
[whimpers]

05:10.792 --> 05:12.375
HARUKA:
Don't worry about Akiko.

05:12.375 --> 05:15.708
I'll be outside the Tower all night
keeping her and the Councilor safe.

05:15.708 --> 05:17.500
‐ You know, Monkey,
once this is all over,

05:17.500 --> 05:20.333
my uncle is going to be
the new Prime Minister.

05:20.333 --> 05:22.000
We'll be living
in the official residence,

05:22.000 --> 05:24.792
and... I'd like you
to live there, too.

05:25.167 --> 05:26.375
Be part of the family.

05:27.208 --> 05:28.167
My family.

05:28.167 --> 05:29.083
‐ Say yes.

05:30.458 --> 05:32.583
Just nod your head.
Your smile is terrifying.

05:32.583 --> 05:33.792
[ooks]

05:34.542 --> 05:35.708
HARUKA:
Okay,

05:35.708 --> 05:37.917
this is as close as I'm gonna be able
to take you.

05:38.833 --> 05:40.167
Be safe up there.

05:40.167 --> 05:41.125
[ooks]

05:41.375 --> 05:43.417
[door handle clicking]

05:44.208 --> 05:45.708
There's a button.

05:45.708 --> 05:46.958
Yeah. To your left.

05:46.958 --> 05:48.083
AKIKO: Yeah. It's the red one.

05:48.083 --> 05:50.167
Just press it down, and the latch
should just come undone.

05:50.167 --> 05:51.000
HARUKA: The red one.
[Monkey growls]

05:51.000 --> 05:53.125
AKIKO: Yeah, no, you're on it. You're‐‐
no, you're touching it right now.

05:53.125 --> 05:54.000
‐ Push the button, man.

05:54.000 --> 05:55.458
HARUKA:
Yeah, right there. No‐‐

05:55.458 --> 05:56.333
‐ Use the‐‐
[grunting]

05:56.333 --> 05:57.417
‐ You're right there!
Red, down, out.

05:57.417 --> 05:58.333
‐ Just push it.
BRYCE: Oh boy.

05:58.333 --> 05:59.667
‐ Push the button.
‐ You just push it‐‐

05:59.667 --> 06:03.000
[overlapping chatter]
[Monkey shrieking]

06:03.000 --> 06:03.750
HARUKA:
The red one.

06:03.750 --> 06:05.167
BRYCE: A hundred of you jerks
could write Hamlet?

06:05.167 --> 06:06.333
AKIKO: You're right there‐‐
BRYCE: Bullshit.

06:06.333 --> 06:06.917
[Monkey shrieking]

06:06.917 --> 06:12.167
♪

06:13.208 --> 06:14.125
TAILOR:
It's a big night.

06:14.583 --> 06:17.417
Will you be attending
any of the election celebrations?

06:17.417 --> 06:19.708
‐ I'll be attending
the only one that matters.

06:19.708 --> 06:21.208
‐ Mm. Mm. Mm.

06:21.208 --> 06:22.750
‐ Oh, look at that!

06:22.750 --> 06:24.375
A literal monkey suit.

06:24.375 --> 06:25.792
TAILOR: Ah, yes.

06:25.792 --> 06:28.458
The monkey is
a very good client.

06:28.458 --> 06:29.500
[both chuckle]

06:29.500 --> 06:31.417
Wears a 24 short.

06:31.667 --> 06:33.958
‐ The guy on the wall
next to the monkey,

06:34.417 --> 06:35.542
he looks familiar.

06:35.542 --> 06:36.875
TAILOR: [scoffs]
American.

06:36.875 --> 06:40.208
I believe his name was Bruce?
Uh, Bryce?

06:40.208 --> 06:42.375
‐ Bryce. Bryce.

06:42.375 --> 06:43.667
He's an assassin.

06:44.125 --> 06:46.167
Hit on me once
at a convention.

06:46.167 --> 06:49.542
Tried to get me into bed
talking about "rifle specs."

06:49.542 --> 06:51.417
[both laugh]

06:51.417 --> 06:53.458
‐ Well, the monkey
certainly likes him.

06:53.750 --> 06:56.542
He was adamant I keep
their photos together.

06:57.458 --> 07:00.042
‐ When's the last time
you saw the American?

07:00.042 --> 07:03.000
I thought I heard he was killed
up in the mountains recently.

07:03.875 --> 07:07.292
‐ Oh, I wouldn't know
anything about that.

07:07.708 --> 07:09.042
‐ Then I believe
we're done here.

07:09.917 --> 07:12.875
Thank you for the dress.
Your craftsmanship is unparalleled.

07:12.875 --> 07:14.458
‐ But I'm still in the middle‐‐

07:14.458 --> 07:15.542
Ah, tch‐tch‐tch‐tch‐tch.

07:16.583 --> 07:17.875
Why did you just poke me?

07:18.292 --> 07:19.833
‐ Oh, I didn't poke you.

07:20.125 --> 07:23.250
I introduced a needle
into your radial artery.

07:23.792 --> 07:26.167
Right now the sharp little guy
is traveling up your arm.

07:26.167 --> 07:27.667
[groans]

07:27.667 --> 07:29.750
‐ He's gonna hang
a right at your shoulder

07:30.917 --> 07:34.375
and arrive at his final destination
any moment.

07:36.958 --> 07:37.667
Now.

07:38.958 --> 07:44.542
♪

07:46.625 --> 07:50.708
♪

07:53.708 --> 07:54.667
[Monkey grunts]

07:54.667 --> 07:56.250
BRYCE:
Oh, hey, I just realized something!

07:56.250 --> 07:58.583
You know how the President has
the First Dog?

07:58.583 --> 08:00.875
Well, that's gonna be you, man.
[Monkey growls]

08:00.875 --> 08:03.083
You're gonna be
the official pet of Japan!

08:03.083 --> 08:04.292
[chuckles]

08:04.292 --> 08:06.292
I mean, they're probably gonna put you
on a goddamn stamp!

08:08.458 --> 08:10.625
Who cares about
the masks anymore.

08:10.625 --> 08:12.292
You're gonna have people licking
your ass‐‐

08:13.542 --> 08:14.458
‐ Huh?

08:15.500 --> 08:17.708
[shrieking]

08:22.875 --> 08:24.792
‐ Dude, I‐I don't know
what's happening,

08:24.792 --> 08:26.667
but it's kinda
freaking me out now.

08:26.667 --> 08:28.625
So, uh, let's just ignore it
and hope it goes away.

08:29.083 --> 08:30.500
You know, like I do
with all my problems.

08:30.500 --> 08:31.708
[indistinct radio chatter]

08:37.792 --> 08:40.667
♪

08:46.250 --> 08:47.000
‐ Huh?

08:47.000 --> 08:48.417
‐ This doesn't make any sense.

08:49.542 --> 08:50.917
It's just confusing,

08:50.917 --> 08:53.000
because if this was
really feudal Japan,

08:53.000 --> 08:56.042
there wouldn't be guys with machine guns
just walking around, you know.

08:56.042 --> 08:58.417
[grunting]

08:58.417 --> 08:59.875
No, I mean,
all I'm saying is that

08:59.875 --> 09:01.833
if you're gonna throw
a theme party, commit.

09:01.833 --> 09:04.083
[Monkey grunting]

09:09.542 --> 09:11.500
Oh shit. Look at this.

09:12.083 --> 09:13.292
Here's where they put
the budget.

09:14.750 --> 09:16.542
Might wanna grab
your katana, dude.

09:18.042 --> 09:19.083
It's time to get bloody.

09:19.083 --> 09:20.750
[roars]

09:27.625 --> 09:29.417
OZU: It shouldn't be this close.

09:30.125 --> 09:31.417
You assured me.

09:31.833 --> 09:32.833
[Bonsai Master sighs]

09:33.208 --> 09:36.042
‐ The polls do not close
for another hour, Councilor.

09:36.042 --> 09:37.583
There's plenty of time.

09:37.583 --> 09:40.542
‐ This is bullshit.
I trusted you.

09:40.542 --> 09:44.000
BONSAI MASTER: Go downstairs,
have a drink, and relax.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.542
It's going to be fine.

09:45.542 --> 09:48.250
‐ The future of our country
is at stake.

09:48.250 --> 09:50.250
How the hell
can you be so calm?

09:50.250 --> 09:53.125
‐ Because I have
an insurance policy.

09:53.583 --> 09:55.500
Now, like I said,

09:55.875 --> 09:57.958
go pour yourself a drink,

09:57.958 --> 09:59.625
mingle with your donors,

10:00.000 --> 10:04.542
and start behaving like
a goddamn Prime Minister.

10:05.208 --> 10:06.458
MERCENARY:
Sir, sir,

10:08.083 --> 10:09.500
the monkey is here.

10:09.500 --> 10:10.792
OZU:
Oh my god.

10:10.792 --> 10:12.750
What are you
talking about, here?

10:13.042 --> 10:14.667
Like here‐here?

10:14.667 --> 10:16.583
BONSAI MASTER:
Get the Councilor to safety.

10:16.583 --> 10:17.667
‐ You're not coming?

10:18.208 --> 10:21.333
‐ I... am capable

10:21.333 --> 10:23.625
of taking care of myself.

10:28.458 --> 10:29.667
‐ Took you long enough.

10:30.042 --> 10:32.333
‐ Hey, there's a lot
of temples in Tokyo.

10:33.042 --> 10:37.750
But only one where
a monkey in a suit hangs out.

10:42.542 --> 10:43.625
‐ I'm sorry.

10:44.042 --> 10:45.542
You will soon meet
your end.

10:46.042 --> 10:48.958
‐ Oh, you make
creepy predictions too?

10:49.375 --> 10:50.542
Didn't see that coming.

10:53.667 --> 10:54.708
‐ Shall we begin?

10:55.292 --> 10:56.583
[clangs]

10:56.583 --> 10:58.875
‐ Oh, this is gonna be fun.

10:58.875 --> 10:59.958
[yells]

11:12.250 --> 11:14.375
Jesus, you're annoying!

11:14.375 --> 11:16.583
‐ You know, if you talk less
when you fight,

11:16.583 --> 11:18.042
you can manage your breath.

11:18.583 --> 11:19.208
[yells]

11:24.708 --> 11:26.167
[tolls loudly]

11:26.667 --> 11:28.125
‐ Aah!

11:29.542 --> 11:32.125
‐ Oh, here we go.

11:32.500 --> 11:34.458
[bell tolls]
[groans]

11:36.750 --> 11:39.708
[tolls]

11:45.625 --> 11:46.917
Bye now.

11:56.583 --> 11:57.958
So, wise man,

11:58.292 --> 12:00.250
is this my end?

12:00.625 --> 12:04.500
‐ It will be when you battle
the monkey and the gho‐‐

12:04.500 --> 12:05.875
‐ The what?
[groans]

12:05.875 --> 12:07.292
Ghost?
‐ No, no, no.

12:07.292 --> 12:08.833
‐ Is that what
you were going to say?

12:08.833 --> 12:09.500
‐ Goat.

12:09.875 --> 12:11.625
Monkey and the goat.

12:11.625 --> 12:12.500
[sighs]

12:12.792 --> 12:13.667
‐ Thanks.

12:13.958 --> 12:17.458
This was very... spiritual.

12:19.042 --> 12:20.083
[Ryoshin groans]

12:33.125 --> 12:36.500
[katanas clanging]

12:38.250 --> 12:39.625
BRYCE:
Look at you go!

12:40.042 --> 12:41.542
Alright, he's coming in high
so aim low!

12:41.542 --> 12:42.375
[Monkey ooks]

12:42.750 --> 12:44.042
Two and three o'clock!
[Monkey screeches]

12:44.042 --> 12:46.500
Oh sorry. Your three o'clock!
I won't do that anymore.

12:46.500 --> 12:47.708
Quick, over your shoulder.

12:48.042 --> 12:50.375
Oh my god.
I wanna throw cash at you.

12:50.792 --> 12:52.583
You know, I had no idea
you could enjoy working

12:52.583 --> 12:53.583
with a partner this much.

12:53.583 --> 12:55.375
Yeah, I just thought they were there
to blame stuff on.

12:58.292 --> 12:59.792
[chuckles]

13:01.250 --> 13:02.417
Ho‐ho‐ho.

13:02.417 --> 13:03.708
Oh man. Oh man.

13:03.708 --> 13:05.250
[thuds]
[Monkey panting]

13:05.250 --> 13:07.458
I guess that's it
for the chips and salsa.

13:07.917 --> 13:10.208
Let's go order us up
a main course.

13:18.125 --> 13:19.500
Hey, keep an eye out
for Lady Bullseye.

13:19.500 --> 13:21.167
She's gotta be lurking
around here somewhere.

13:21.167 --> 13:22.750
[growling]

13:23.583 --> 13:24.000
Whoa!

13:26.375 --> 13:28.292
‐ You've come
a long way, Monkey.

13:28.292 --> 13:30.250
‐ Yeah, back to the 1600s,
by the look of it.

13:30.250 --> 13:33.208
‐ So, are you here
to return the katana

13:33.208 --> 13:34.708
I gifted to General Kato?

13:35.417 --> 13:36.583
Or perhaps

13:37.333 --> 13:39.042
you'd like to meet
its sister!

13:39.042 --> 13:40.208
[ooks]

13:40.208 --> 13:42.292
You don't know it,
but you hold in your hands

13:42.292 --> 13:43.583
the blade of a hero.

13:44.042 --> 13:46.500
Saigō Takamori was the last
of the great Samurai.

13:47.000 --> 13:50.417
He died fighting against
the modernization of our country.

13:50.417 --> 13:53.417
A transition he knew
would lead to mediocrity

13:53.417 --> 13:54.708
and cowardice!

13:54.708 --> 13:55.375
[grunts]

13:57.625 --> 14:00.583
But I've made a vow
to continue his fight.

14:04.042 --> 14:05.542
To bring back the old ways

14:05.542 --> 14:08.875
and restore Japan
to its proper place of honor.

14:08.875 --> 14:11.542
‐ I'm sorry, is his fighting style
to bore us to death?

14:12.917 --> 14:13.958
BONSAI MASTER:
And now,

14:14.958 --> 14:17.083
all that stands in my way

14:17.667 --> 14:18.667
is you.

14:19.250 --> 14:20.417
[yells]

14:20.417 --> 14:22.125
[shrieking]

14:22.125 --> 14:24.792
‐ Go for his nuts! You know?
Just swing it around his nuts!

14:27.375 --> 14:30.333
‐ You must control
your breath, Monkey.

14:30.333 --> 14:31.083
[Monkey shrieks]

14:37.042 --> 14:39.667
BONSAI MASTER:
Tension will get you killed, Monkey.

14:46.500 --> 14:47.583
[whimpers]

14:49.167 --> 14:51.792
[chuckles] Good monkey.

14:51.792 --> 14:53.167
‐ Okay, okay, don't panic.

14:53.167 --> 14:54.708
Hey, this tree is pretty sweet.

14:54.708 --> 14:56.292
You know, he probably kills
everyone under it.

14:56.292 --> 14:57.708
Maybe if you climbed inside,
you could‐‐

14:58.667 --> 14:59.583
What the‐‐

15:00.667 --> 15:02.958
Hey! Hey! Did you see that!
[ooks]

15:02.958 --> 15:05.292
Did you see what I did?
Look what I‐I‐‐ I broke the tree.

15:05.542 --> 15:07.333
I broke the tree
with my, with my ghost hands.

15:07.833 --> 15:09.500
What the‐‐ aw, crap.

15:09.500 --> 15:10.917
I swear to God I did it.

15:10.917 --> 15:12.292
[ooks, screeches]

15:12.292 --> 15:13.417
‐ Ugh.

15:13.417 --> 15:16.292
Keep your filthy hands off of it!

15:16.542 --> 15:18.125
[yells]

15:18.125 --> 15:19.292
[roars]

15:20.250 --> 15:21.208
[gasps]

15:21.542 --> 15:22.500
No.

15:22.792 --> 15:23.583
[shrieks]

15:25.292 --> 15:27.333
[screams]

15:28.083 --> 15:29.958
[groaning]

15:39.333 --> 15:41.167
[groaning]

15:41.917 --> 15:44.667
You've defeated me.

15:45.333 --> 15:46.375
[groans]

15:47.083 --> 15:48.875
But it doesn't matter.

15:50.708 --> 15:52.542
The die is cast.

15:52.542 --> 15:53.792
[groans]

15:53.792 --> 15:56.167
♪

16:01.125 --> 16:04.083
A man who toils
for his country

16:05.417 --> 16:07.208
will always be lit

16:07.708 --> 16:10.208
by the sun of Japan.

16:10.708 --> 16:11.667
[grunts]

16:12.667 --> 16:13.750
[groans]

16:13.750 --> 16:15.333
‐ Oh‐ho‐ho‐oh whoa.

16:16.125 --> 16:17.125
Yikes.

16:17.125 --> 16:18.417
Someone had
a big lunch.

16:18.417 --> 16:19.250
[whimpers]

16:22.167 --> 16:23.833
[people shouting]

16:37.750 --> 16:39.750
POLICE CAPTAIN:
This crowd is getting out of control.

16:39.750 --> 16:40.833
We need more backup.

16:40.833 --> 16:42.083
‐ Forget the crowd.

16:42.083 --> 16:44.333
What about Lady Bullseye?
She could be anywhere.

16:44.333 --> 16:45.375
SILVER SAMURAI:
Oy!

16:45.667 --> 16:48.042
You thought
you could have a party

16:48.875 --> 16:52.583
and not invite
the Silver Samurai?

16:52.583 --> 16:54.542
‐ Who is that?
‐ Holster your weapon.

16:54.958 --> 16:56.667
That's Silver Samurai.

16:56.667 --> 16:58.542
He's a mutant medieval warrior

16:58.542 --> 17:01.208
and sworn protector
of the Prime Minister

17:01.208 --> 17:02.958
and a giant asshole.

17:02.958 --> 17:04.000
[Silver Samurai chuckles]

17:04.667 --> 17:06.042
‐ My people,

17:06.042 --> 17:09.792
tonight I stand here
not in service to one candidate

17:09.792 --> 17:11.708
but all of Japan.

17:12.042 --> 17:14.417
Whatever the outcome
of this election,

17:14.417 --> 17:17.333
there will be peace
in the streets.

17:17.875 --> 17:21.333
So says
the Silver Samurai!

17:21.333 --> 17:22.958
OFFICER:
What the hell is that?

17:24.542 --> 17:26.917
‐ I am Yuki!

17:27.292 --> 17:29.958
The undead ghost assassin.

17:31.042 --> 17:35.833
I will restore peace to Tokyo!

17:36.333 --> 17:37.333
‐ Yuki.

17:38.667 --> 17:40.208
[growls]

17:40.625 --> 17:42.083
‐ Wow. This is just great.

17:42.083 --> 17:44.042
This is a...
a total shit‐show.

17:44.042 --> 17:45.833
‐ Ha! Yeah.

17:45.833 --> 17:48.958
[crowd cheering in distance]

17:55.958 --> 17:56.958
‐ Akiko.

17:57.875 --> 17:58.917
It's time.

18:00.875 --> 18:04.208
‐ We've just gotten word that
the final election results are in.

18:08.583 --> 18:10.000
I'm proud to announce

18:11.708 --> 18:14.083
the new Prime Minister
of Japan

18:15.292 --> 18:17.167
is Shinji Yokohama.

18:17.167 --> 18:19.958
[cheering]

18:19.958 --> 18:20.625
AKIKO:
Yes!

18:20.625 --> 18:22.250
Whoo!
[laughs]

18:22.250 --> 18:24.833
Oh my god! Uncle! Yes!

18:24.833 --> 18:25.917
You deserve this!

18:25.917 --> 18:27.333
‐ We deserve this.

18:27.333 --> 18:29.208
I couldn't have done it
without you.

18:29.208 --> 18:32.042
‐ Oh, I wrote something
for your acceptance speech.

18:32.042 --> 18:32.917
It's awesome.

18:32.917 --> 18:35.875
‐ No offense,
but I wrote my own.

18:35.875 --> 18:38.125
‐ Oh, so you're
firing me again?

18:38.125 --> 18:41.292
‐ No, Akiko.
You're my new chief of staff.

18:41.625 --> 18:42.500
‐ Uncle‐‐

18:43.042 --> 18:43.792
‐ Don't.

18:43.792 --> 18:46.792
If you cry,
you're gonna make me cry.

18:46.792 --> 18:48.708
‐ Prime Minister!
[laughs]

18:48.708 --> 18:50.208
Come on,
let's get you a drink!

18:55.125 --> 18:58.583
[Akiko sobs quietly]

19:02.125 --> 19:03.083
[sighs]

19:12.583 --> 19:13.458
[door opens]

19:16.167 --> 19:19.250
♪ ominous music playing ♪

19:19.250 --> 19:20.667
‐ Oh, sweetie,

19:21.417 --> 19:22.708
let me help you
with that.

19:22.708 --> 19:23.792
‐ Oh, uh‐‐

19:24.292 --> 19:27.875
Uh... um, I'm good,
but thank you.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.417
‐ I insist.

19:29.417 --> 19:30.875
‐ Oh. Just gonna do it.

19:30.875 --> 19:34.792
Um... I guess my hands are
kinda shaky right now.

19:34.792 --> 19:35.833
‐ I know!

19:36.167 --> 19:38.167
What an exciting night!

19:39.083 --> 19:40.875
Yikes. What happened here?

19:41.708 --> 19:43.375
‐ It's a long story.

19:45.333 --> 19:47.375
It's still
a little tender.

19:47.375 --> 19:48.458
‐ Aw.

19:49.417 --> 19:52.708
I'll be very... gentle.

19:56.083 --> 19:58.375
♪

19:58.375 --> 19:59.625
[grunts]

20:00.833 --> 20:03.792
‐ I mean, I snapped that branch,
you know. I‐I‐‐ But how?

20:04.167 --> 20:06.792
Look, this is all a sign that
something big's about to happen, you know.

20:06.792 --> 20:09.292
The barriers between the worlds,
they're breaking, you know.

20:09.292 --> 20:12.833
Like my, my presence here is,
it's starting to fray. I can feel it.

20:12.833 --> 20:14.958
♪

20:16.125 --> 20:18.833
[katana scraping]

20:21.458 --> 20:25.417
[tapping]

20:28.708 --> 20:29.625
‐ Oh God.

20:30.500 --> 20:31.250
You?

20:31.917 --> 20:33.750
I just lost
the election!

20:33.750 --> 20:35.417
Isn't that enough?
[Monkey ooking]

20:37.333 --> 20:39.000
‐ So now you're going
to kill me,

20:39.833 --> 20:41.333
just like you killed Takahara.

20:41.333 --> 20:43.583
[growling, screeching]

20:43.583 --> 20:44.333
Me?

20:44.792 --> 20:46.958
Why would I have done it?

20:46.958 --> 20:49.750
I was ten points up
in the polls against Ken!

20:50.250 --> 20:53.708
Suddenly he's murdered,
and I'm running against a martyr!

20:54.250 --> 20:55.667
Who could compete
with that?

20:56.000 --> 20:57.125
Think about it!

20:57.667 --> 20:59.000
Who had
the most to gain?

20:59.000 --> 21:00.792
[growls]

21:02.958 --> 21:05.125
‐ Hey, look, as much
as I hate this scumbag,

21:05.125 --> 21:06.208
he's making a good point.

21:06.708 --> 21:09.792
'Cause all Ken's death did
was open the door for, um‐‐

21:09.792 --> 21:10.917
[crowd cheering]

21:10.917 --> 21:12.042
Oh my god.

21:13.000 --> 21:13.958
[crowd cheering]

21:13.958 --> 21:16.125
‐ Thank you! Thank you!

21:16.625 --> 21:19.875
A great friend of mine
once said,

21:19.875 --> 21:22.500
"He who toils
for his country

21:22.500 --> 21:24.625
"will always be lit

21:24.625 --> 21:26.750
by the sun of Japan."

21:28.000 --> 21:29.250
‐ Oh shit.

21:32.708 --> 21:37.042
♪ dramatic theme playing ♪

21:37.042 --> 21:41.375
♪
